snippet.title: Best desktops
snippet.description: CNET's reviews of the best desktop computers include photos, video, and user reviews.

snippet.title: Roku LT (2013)
snippet.description: The Roku LT is the best budget streaming-media device, easily topping the $35 Chromecast.

snippet.title: Fujifilm X-T1
snippet.description: The Fujifilm X-T1 is a great camera for advanced photographers as long as its quirks don't bother you.

snippet.title: FIFA 14 review
snippet.description: This is easily the best sports game on mobile devices, bringing realistic soccer to your touch screen and a ton of content and game modes to explore.

snippet.title: NAD Electronics D 3020 Hybrid Digital Amplifier
snippet.description: If you're looking to ditch your giant AV receiver for a compact stereo amp, the NAD D 3020 is the one to get.

snippet.title: WhatsApp Messenger
snippet.description: Though you only get a few extra useful features, WhatsApp Messenger is an excellent choice for sending free texts across platforms, even internationally.

snippet.title: Samsung Galaxy S5
snippet.description: Subtly improved and smartly refined, the Samsung Galaxy S5 is a superior superphone that hits every mark but the sharpest design.

snippet.title: RS120
snippet.description: The company's 2014 flagship, dubbed the Reference Series, combines a host of enhancements and offers a truly gigantic 120-inch size in support of its bombastic claim.

snippet.title: JVC DLA-X700R
snippet.description: If you can afford the JVC DLA-X700R -- and the dedicated room, high-quality screen, and professional calibration required to make it shine -- its spectacular picture quality is worth the steep investment.

snippet.title: Plantronics BackBeat Fit
snippet.description: The BackBeat Fit may not be perfect, but it's one of the best wireless sports headphones available.
